$q6 = Formula("1");

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
\{ ans_rule(20) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
$PAR
For \(\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{n^2+1},\) we want to
compare to the series \(\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{2n^2},\) which
we know converges by the \(p\)-series test.
Which one of the estimates is the correct one to use in comparison test?
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

